key_statement.statement:
Phyllaries oblong or ovate to spatulate or linear-spatulate (not carinate);
        cypselae obconic, slightly compressed, ribs 5 (pericarps sometimes with myxogenic cells);
        pappi 0, coroniform, or adaxial auricles

Cypselae dimorphic: outer (ray) usually 3-angled and ± winged (except Mauranthemum
        ); inner (disc) ± compressed-prismatic or ± flattened (angles winged), or ± quadrate (1 or 2
        angles sometimes winged), or columnar (not winged).
